f%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Faging-retirement-japan-social-security-financial-insecurity-working-at-80-2025-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eaging%20population%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20offset%20healthcare%20workers'%20retirements.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%2C%20other%20industries%20like%20construction%20are%20facing%20a%20retirement%20cliff%3A%20Highly%20skilled%20baby%20boomer%20workers%20like%20plumbers%20and%20electricians%20are%20leaving%20the%20workforce%2C%20and%20there%20aren't%20enough%20young%20workers%20coming%20in%20to%20fill%20in%20the%20gaps.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Caside%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDid%20you%20make%20a%20career%20pivot%20into%20skilled%20trades%3F%20Reach%20out%20to%20this%20reporter%20to%20share%20what%20that%20was%20like%2C%20at%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22mailto%3Amhoff%40businessinsider.com%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emhoff%40businessinsider.com%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3C%2Faside%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere's%20a%20lot%20of%20uncertainty%20about%20how%20much%20AI%20will%20affect%20the%20workplace%20over%20time%20and%20what%20will%20be%20automated%20or%20replaced%20completely%2C%20even%20in%20healthcare.%20There's%20more%20certainty%20that%20aging%20is%20a%20structural%20issue%20that%20will%20continue%20to%20affect%20employers'%20needs.%20The%20Bureau%20of%20Labor%20Statistics%20said%20the%20aging%20population%20will%20mean%20more%20demand%20for%20long-term%20care%20and%20therapy%20services.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAI%20may%20be%20the%20economy's%20future%2C%20but%20aging%20is%20its%20present%2C%26quot%3B%20Richardson%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22004141ee-2aab-4383-89d4-f4d92d1e7dfe%5C%22%3EThe%20boom%20of%20home%20health%20and%20personal%20care%20aides%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EDemand%20for%20home%20health%20and%20personal%20care%20aides%20is%20set%20to%20boom%3B%20BLS%20estimates%20employment%20in%20this%20already%20large%20occupation%20will%20increase%20by%20739%2C800%20between%202024%20and%202034%2C%20more%20than%20any%20other%20career.%20Richardson%20said%20we're%20pretty%20far%20from%20the%20futuristic%20experiences%20of%20%26quot%3BThe%20Jetsons.%26quot%3B%20She%20said%20large%20language%20models%20aren't%20lifting%20patients%20or%20taking%20them%20on%20a%20walk.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-become-travel-nurse-salaries-avoid-burnout-contract-gig-work-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EHealthcare%20employment%3C%2Fa%3E%20has%20been%20growing%20steadily%20regardless%20of%20the%20business%20cycle%20for%20decades%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Joshua%20Gottlieb%2C%20an%20economist%20and%20a%20professor%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Chicago.%20%26quot%3BThat's%20just%20been%20a%20very%20stable%20trend.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENurse%20practitioners%20and%20registered%20nurses%20are%20also%20expected%20to%20see%20employment%20rise%20a%20lot%20over%20the%20decade%2C%20but%20Susan%20Grant%2C%20chief%20clinical%20officer%20at%20healthcare-operations%20platform%20Symplr%2C%20said%20nursing%20has%20faced%20shortages%2C%20high%20turnover%2C%20and%20challenges%20with%20building%20a%20talent%20pipeline%2C%20as%20some%20professionals%20retired%20early%20during%20the%20pandemic%20and%20because%20of%20faculty%20shortages.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Caside%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDid%20you%20make%20a%20career%20pivot%20into%20a%20healthcare%20job%3F%20Reach%20out%20to%20this%20reporter%20to%20share%20what%20that%20was%20like%2C%20at%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22mailto%3Amhoff%40businessinsider.com%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emhoff%40businessinsider.com%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3C%2Faside%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere%20are%20major%20cost%20issues%20within%20the%20healthcare%20systems%2C%20and%20cost%20cutting%20and%20a%20major%20focus%20on%20efficiencies%20in%20the%20health%20systems%2C%26quot%3B%20Grant%20said%2C%20adding%2C%20%26quot%3Bbecause%20nursing%20is%20such%20a%20large%20part%20of%20the%20healthcare%20workforce%2C%20staffing%20has%20been%20a%20major%20focus%2C%20and%20labor%20costs%20are%20very%20high%2C%20and%20turnover%20actually%20contributes%20to%20those%20costs.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20pay%20for%20these%20healthcare%20jobs%20varies.%20BLS%20data%20showed%20the%20median%20annual%20wage%20for%20home%20health%20and%20personal%20care%20aides%20was%20%2434%2C900%20in%202024%2C%20short%20of%20the%20national%20median%20of%20%2449%2C500.%20Meanwhile%2C%20the%20median%20for%20registered%20nurses%20was%20%2493%2C600%2C%20and%20for%20nurse%20practitioners%20was%20%24129%2C210.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22f860e096-36e3-48a8-b9ca-f0a6632c656b%5C%22%3EAging%20is%20likely%20to%20affect%20demand%20for%20unpaid%20and%20informal%20care%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EMany%20Americans%20already%20help%20their%20parents%20or%20grandparents%20with%20appointments%2C%20meals%2C%20and%20other%20activities%20%E2%80%94%20while%20they%20hold%20a%20job.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EKaren%20Lee-Coss%2C%20who%20is%20in%20her%2050s%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcaregiving-balance-full-time-job-caring-for-mom-teens-family-2025-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ecares%20for%20her%20mother%3C%2Fa%3E.%20She%20takes%20her%20on%20outings%20and%20helps%20her%20with%20bathing%20and%20skincare.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20take%20care%20of%20her%20the%20way%20that%20I%20would%20want%20someone%20to%20take%20care%20of%20me%2C%26quot%3B%20Lee-Coss%20said.%20%26quot%3BI%20know%20the%20state%20my%20mother%20lived%20in%20before%20she%20got%20sick%2C%20and%20I%20always%20want%20to%20maintain%20that.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELee-Coss%20said%20caregiving%20requires%20different%20hats%2C%20but%20she%20has%20to%20know%20when%20to%20take%20those%20off.%20%26quot%3BWhen%20my%20children%20want%20to%20have%20a%20conversation%2C%20I%20have%20to%20know%20how%20to%20take%20the%20caregiver%20hat%20for%20my%20mother%20off%20and%20put%20the%20mother%20hat%20for%20my%20children%20on%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Lee-Coss.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Bureau%20of%20Labor%20Statistics%20found%2C%20using%202023%20and%202024%20data%2C%20that%2038%20million%20Americans%20did%20some%20kind%20of%20unpaid%20eldercare.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BMy%20bet%20is%20that%20informal%20sector%20is%20going%20to%20grow%20as%20people%20age%2C%26quot%3B%20Richardson%20said.%20She%20said%20we%20already%20have%20a%20lot%20of%20instances%20of%20informal%20work%2C%20such%20as%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsell-clutter-pay-for-date-night-babysitters-facebook-marketplace-2025-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ebabysitter%20coming%20over%3C%2Fa%3E.%20%26quot%3BYou'll%20probably%20see%20more%20of%20that%20informality%20where%20people%20are%20not%20really%20working%20for%20employers%20or%20institutions%2C%20but%20they're%20just%20working%20for%20their%20neighbors%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BIt%20might%20be%20sporadic%20and%20occasional%2C%20but%20it's%20helping%20meet%20a%20need%20in%20their%20communities.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%220331f338-c2ec-4c0c-88e3-f26e80e8d41a%5C%22%3EAging%20is%20going%20to%20affect%20all%20kinds%20of%20work%2C%20such%20as%20the%20construction%20sector%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere%20is%20no%20part%20of%20the%20labor%20market%20that%20is%20immune%20from%20the%20aging%20demographic%2C%26quot%3B%20Richardson%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETake%20construction.%20The%20sector%20is%20about%20a%20third%20the%20size%20of%20healthcare%20and%20social%20assistance%2C%20but%20has%20grown%20over%20the%20years%2C%20recovering%20from%20the%20Great%20Recession%20and%202020%20pandemic%20losses.%20It%20hit%20a%20record%20employment%20level%20this%20past%20March.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStill%2C%20people%20aging%20out%20has%20consequences%20for%20the%20sector.%20Home%20Builders%20Institute's%20president%20and%20CEO%2C%20Ed%20Brady%2C%20said%20more%20older%20tradespeople%20are%20leaving%20than%20younger%20people%20coming%20in%2C%20deepening%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhousing-crisis-national-shortage-construction-workers-job-demand-2024-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Elabor%20shortage%3C%2Fa%3E%20issue%2C%20but%20also%20affecting%20the%20productivity%2C%20quality%2C%20and%20speed%20that%20the%20older%2C%20experienced%20workers%20had.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe've%20got%20a%20long%20runway%20to%20overcome%20and%20populate%20the%20next%20generation%20of%20these%20skilled%20laborers%2C%26quot%3B%20Brady%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBased%20on%20ADP%20data%2C%20the%20average%20age%20of%20an%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhvac-technician-skipped-college-doesnt-worry-about-ai-2026-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EHVAC%20worker%3C%2Fa%3E%20has%20dropped%20from%2041%20in%20June%202020%20to%2037%20in%20June%202025.%20%26quot%3BThat's%20not%20because%20a%20bunch%20of%20new%20people%20became%20HVAC%20workers%3B%20it's%20because%20older%20workers%20are%20retiring%2C%26quot%3B%20Richardson%20said.%20The%20average%20ages%20have%20also%20fallen%20for%20other%20skilled%20trades%2C%20including%20from%2044%20to%2039%20for%20electricians%20and%2040%20to%2036%20for%20plumbers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20often%20said%20that%20demographics%20is%20destiny%2C%20and%20that's%20likely%20to%20be%20the%20story%20for%20the%20job%20market%20for%20years%20to%20come.%20%26quot%3BAI%20deserves%20a%20lot%20of%20attention%2C%20but%20aging%20is%20the%20thing%20that%20we%20can%20see%20right%20now%2C%26quot%3B%20Richardson%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-aging-ai-reshaping-job-market-2026-4%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1777196161000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69ebd92b3fecbb42897a3f00%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-aging-ai-reshaping-job-market-2026-4%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22There's%20a%20lot%20of%20emphasis%20on%20what%20AI%20means%20for%20the%20job%20market.%20Aging%20Americans%20are%20already%20having%20a%20larger%20effect.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22insider%40insider.com%20(Madison%20Hoff)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Amazon%20sellers%20say%20they're%20fed%20up%20with%20policy%20and%20fee%20changes%3A%20'It's%20like%20death%20by%20a%20thousand%20cuts'%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223680%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22amazon%20boxes%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69eba8283fecbb42897a3c97%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222397%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EAmazon%20sellers%20say%20they've%20been%20hit%20with%20multiple%20policy%20changes%20all%20at%20once.%3Cp%3EBloomberg%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EAmazon%20sellers%20say%20they've%20been%20frustrated%20with%20recent%20policy%20changes%20on%20the%20e-commerce%20site.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EA%20change%20announced%20in%20April%20regarding%20ad%20payments%20sparked%20a%20sellers'%20boycott.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EAs%20a%20result%2C%20sellers%20are%20diversifying%20their%20sales%20channels%2C%20using%20platforms%20like%20Shopify%20and%20TikTok.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20April%202%2C%20some%20Amazon%20sellers%20got%20an%20email%20that%20many%20saw%20as%20a%20breaking%20point.%20Starting%20April%2015%2C%20Amazon%20said%2C%20their%20advertising%20costs%20would%20be%20deducted%20from%20their%20retail%20proceeds%20first%2C%20with%20a%20credit%20or%20debit%20card%20used%20only%20as%20a%20backup%20if%20those%20proceeds%20fell%20short.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20sellers%20already%20contending%20with%20delayed%20payouts%20and%20new%20fees%2C%20the%20change%20felt%20like%20the%20last%20straw.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUnder%20the%20old%20setup%2C%20sellers%20could%20pay%20for%20advertising%20on%20a%20credit%20card%2C%20collect%20points%2C%20and%20benefit%20from%20the%20extra%20time%20before%20the%20bill%20came%20due.%20Under%20the%20new%20approach%2C%20ad%20costs%20would%20come%20out%20of%20proceeds%20first%2C%20reducing%20float%20and%20tightening%20cash%20flow.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAd%20spend%20is%20one%20of%20the%20biggest%20expenses%20for%20many%20sellers%2C%20said%20Eugene%20Khayman%2C%20founder%20of%20Million%20Dollar%20Sellers%2C%20a%20network%20of%20more%20than%20800%20e-commerce%20founders%20doing%20nearly%20%2415%20billion%20in%20annual%20Amazon%20revenue.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhen%20you're%20getting%204%25%20cash%20back%20on%20your%20third-largest%20expense%20in%20the%20business%2C%20ads%2C%20you%20can%20live%20off%20of%20that%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20told%20Business%20Insider.%20%26quot%3BYou%20can%20pay%20an%20extra%20person%20a%20salary.%20You%20can%20invest%20more%20in%20the%20business.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAmazon%20later%20announced%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fadvertising.amazon.com%2Fen-us%2Flibrary%2Fnews%2Fupdate-on-advertiser-payments%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eit%20would%20delay%20the%20change%20to%20ad%20payments%3C%2Fa%3E%20until%20August%201%2C%202026.%20The%20company%20also%20offered%20sellers%20a%20%242%2C500%20promotional%20ad%20credit%2C%20Khayman%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20statement%20to%20Business%20Insider%2C%20Amazon%20said%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%26quot%3B%3C%2Fem%3EWe%20are%20committed%20to%20supporting%20the%20success%20of%20selling%20partners%20in%20our%20store%20and%20continue%20to%20help%20them%20achieve%20record%20sales%20year%20after%20year.%20We%20invest%20heavily%20in%20powerful%20tools%2C%20services%2C%20and%20programs%20to%20enable%20their%20business%20growth%20at%20a%20cost%20that%20is%20typically%20lower%20than%20alternatives.%20The%20recent%20changes%20to%20advertising%20payment%20methods%20and%20reserve%20settings%20align%20a%20small%20subset%20of%20sellers%20with%20standard%20practices%20already%20used%20by%20an%20overwhelming%20majority%20of%20our%20selling%20partners.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%222b3b0b36-f3ad-48dc-93a9-1af8e537c8c3%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3E'Death%20by%20a%20thousand%20cuts'%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EKhayman%20said%20the%20April%20email%20circulated%20quickly%20through%20the%20MDS%20community%20because%20it%20followed%20several%20other%20changes%20in%20a%20short%20period.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BA%20lot%20of%20people%20were%20very%20frustrated%20because%20it's%20like%20the%20fourth%20change%20they%20made%20in%20a%20matter%20of%20a%20month.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAmong%20the%20most%20consequential%20recent%20changes%2C%20Khayman%20cited%20three%20in%20particular%3A%20Amazon%20delaying%20when%20sellers%20receive%20their%20money%2C%20a%203.5%25%20fuel%20and%20logistics-related%20surcharge%2C%20and%20the%20ads%20payment%20change.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAmazon's%20DD%2B7%20(delivery%20date%20%2B%207%20days)%20policy%2C%20which%20holds%20seller%20payments%20for%20seven%20days%20after%20an%20order%20is%20delivered%2C%20creates%20a%20cash-flow%20problem%2C%20said%20Aaron%20Biner%2C%20founder%20of%20Little%20Jupiter%2C%20a%20kids'%20brand%20that%20sells%20plush%20toys%20and%20arts%20and%20crafts.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20Amazon's%20paying%20you%20slower%2C%20you're%20going%20to%20think%20twice%20before%20you%20launch%20a%20new%20product%20or%20think%20about%20adding%20more%20styles%20or%20different%20colors%20onto%20a%20product%2C%26quot%3B%20Biner%20said.%20%26quot%3BBecause%20you've%20got%20to%20support%20each%20one%20of%20those%20with%20solid%20cash%20flow%20financials.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20is%20just%20one%20of%20several%20pressures%20sellers%20say%20they%20are%20facing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBiner%20said%20he%20tracked%2016%20fee%20increases%2C%20added%20fees%2C%20or%20lost%20perks%20between%202021%20and%20the%20change%20that's%20slated%20for%20August%202026.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BDuring%20that%20same%20period%2C%20there%20were%2010%20small%20positive%20changes%20for%20sellers%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said%2C%20classifying%20most%20of%20them%20as%20%26quot%3Bgive-backs%2C%20to%20soften%20the%20blow%20of%20the%20negative%20changes.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20years%2C%20selling%20on%20Amazon%20has%20felt%20like%20%26quot%3Bdeath%20by%20a%20thousand%20cuts%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20He%20compared%20avoiding%20extra%20fees%20to%20navigating%20a%20fast%20car%20down%20a%20narrow%20lane.%20%26quot%3BThere%20is%20almost%20no%20room%20for%20error.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAlex%20Yale%2C%20who%20runs%20the%20cleaning%20product%20brand%20Uncle%20Todd's%2C%20said%20the%20pressure%20is%20not%20coming%20from%20a%20single%20source.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20feels%20like%20a%20continuous%2C%20almost%20a%20multi-front%20margin%20squeeze%20and%20not%20just%20like%20a%20single%20policy%20change%2C%26quot%3B%20Yale%20said.%20Each%20new%20fee%20or%20policy%20change%20may%20be%20survivable%20on%20its%20own%2C%20but%20%26quot%3Bif%20you%20look%20at%20the%20compounding%20effect%20on%20these%20already%20thin%20margins%2C%20that%20becomes%20a%20very%20dangerous%20proposition.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20frustration%20culminated%20in%20an%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cnbc.com%2F2026%2F04%2F15%2Famazon-sellers-boycott-ads-payment-changes.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EApril%2015%20ad%20boycott%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20in%20which%20some%20sellers%20paused%20Amazon%20advertising%20for%20a%20day%20to%20get%20the%20company's%20attention.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%227602f746-3246-413a-b686-50880214109b%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3ERethinking%20life%20beyond%20Amazon%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20answer%20to%20tighter%20margins%20is%20not%20as%20simple%20as%20raising%20prices.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20I%20go%20from%20%2410%20to%20%2411.50%20to%20offset%20my%20increase%20in%20costs%2C%20am%20I%20then%20going%20to%20be%20the%20most%20expensive%20option%2C%20or%20a%20more%20expensive%20option%2C%20and%20thus%20lose%20conversion%20rate%20on%20Amazon%3F%20Am%20I%20going%20to%20lose%20sales%20velocity%3F%20Am%20I%20going%20to%20lose%20ranking%20on%20the%20Amazon%20page%3F%26quot%3B%20Yale%20said.%20%26quot%3BThe%20answer%20is%20probably%20yes.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBiner%20offered%20a%20concrete%20example.%20One%20of%20his%20plush%20toys%2C%20which%20sold%20for%20roughly%20%2416.99%20to%20%2417.99%20in%202019%2C%20now%20sells%20for%20%2423.49%2C%20but%20the%20higher%20price%20has%20not%20solved%20the%20problem.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAs%20we've%20increased%20the%20prices%2C%20we've%20sold%20fewer%20units%2C%20and%20we've%20made%20less%20money%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20sellers%2C%20including%20Rich%20Tesoriero%2C%20who%20sells%20floral%20handbags%2C%20are%20trying%20to%20become%20less%20dependent%20on%20Amazon.%20He's%20an%20Amazon%20veteran%2C%20having%20sold%20on%20the%20platform%20since%202008%2C%20but%20recently%2C%20it's%20become%20exhausting%20to%20manage.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAmazon%20has%20become%2C%20for%20me%2C%20sort%20of%20this%20whack-a-mole%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BYou%20solve%20one%20problem%2C%20another%20one%20pops%20up.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETesoriero%20said%20he%20is%20increasingly%20focused%20on%20building%20outside%20Amazon.%20About%2020%25%20of%20his%20revenue%20came%20from%20Shopify%20last%20year%3B%20in%20the%20first%20quarter%20of%202026%2C%20he%20said%2C%20that%20figure%20rose%20to%2035%25.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBiner%20added%20that%20many%20sellers%20are%20also%20experimenting%20with%20channels%20like%20TikTok.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhen%20you%20feel%20like%20a%20business%20isn't%20hearing%20you%2C%20loud%20and%20clear%2C%20like%20Amazon%2C%20that%20pushes%20a%20lot%20of%20people%20to%20try%20to%20innovate%20their%20business%2C%26quot%3B%20Biner%20said.%20%26quot%3BNecessity%20is%20the%20mother%20of%20invention.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2294c48cb7-58db-4492-8824-bead0d8649de%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3E'Amazon%20is%20a%20frenemy'%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20all%20their%20complaints%2C%20the%20sellers%20Business%20Insider%20spoke%20with%20were%20careful%20to%20say%20they%20are%20not%20anti-Amazon.%20Many%20still%20rely%20heavily%20on%20the%20platform%2C%20and%20several%20credited%20it%20with%20helping%20them%20build%20successful%20businesses.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETesoriero%2C%20a%20former%20engineer%20who%20now%20runs%20his%20e-commerce%20business%20full-time%20with%20his%20wife%2C%20put%20it%20simply%3A%20%26quot%3BAmazon%20is%20a%20frenemy.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BMy%20greatest%20successes%20and%20frustrations%20come%20from%20Amazon%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20sellers%20who%20can%20adapt%2C%20Amazon's%20tougher%20environment%20may%20present%20an%20opportunity.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20is%20an%20exciting%20time%20in%20a%20way%20because%20we%20hear%20that%20the%20number%20of%20sellers%20is%20going%20down%2C%26quot%3B%20Tesoriero%20said.%20%26quot%3BAnd%20so%20the%20people%20who%20have%20the%20operational%20skill%2C%20this%20is%20an%20opportunity%20to%20grow%20their%20business.%20I'm%20still%20optimistic.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20survive%2C%20many%20sellers%20lean%20on%20communities%20like%20MDS%2C%20which%20members%20described%20as%20a%20kind%20of%20collective%20brain.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIn%20this%20community%2C%20we%20don't%20really%20have%20a%20union%2C%26quot%3B%20Biner%20said.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20the%20closest%20thing%20we%20have%20to%20a%20group%20voice.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20sellers%20who%20feel%20increasingly%20squeezed%2C%20that%20kind%20of%20shared%20knowledge%20may%20be%20becoming%20almost%20as%20essential%20as%20Amazon%20itself.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famazon-sellers-top-frustrations-ad-payments-challenges-eommerce-2026-4%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1777196101000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69eba8593fecbb42897a3c99%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famazon-sellers-top-frustrations-ad-payments-challenges-eommerce-2026-4%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22One%20seller%20says%20avoiding%20Amazon%20fees%20is%20like%20navigating%20a%20fast%20car%20down%20a%20narrow%20lane.%20%26quot%3BThere%20is%20almost%20no%20room%20for%20error.%26quot%3B%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22kelkins%40businessinsider.com%20(Kathleen%20Elkins)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22I%20drive%20for%20a%20ride-hailing%20cooperative%20for%20extra%20cash%20instead%20of%20Uber%20or%20Lyft%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Daniel%20Mondragon%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69deb235d06bf1b901273aa3%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22960%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EDaniel%20Mondragon%20drives%20for%20a%20ride-hailing%20cooperative%20in%20Colorado.%3Cp%3EMatthew%20DeFeo%20for%20BI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3ESome%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fuber-lyft-drivers-joining-making-apps-cooperatives-rideshare-2025-2%5C%22%20data-autoaffiliated%3D%5C%22false%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eride-hailing%20drivers%3C%2Fa%3E%20are%20creating%20their%20own%20apps%20rather%20than%20driving%20for%20Uber%20or%20Lyft.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EDaniel%20Mondragon%20drives%20for%20one%20such%20app%20in%20Colorado.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20approach%20gives%20him%20flexibility%20while%20earning%20a%20greater%20share%20of%20each%20ride%2C%20he%20said.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20as-told-to%20essay%20is%20based%20on%20a%20conversation%20with%20Daniel%20Mondragon%2C%20a%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdriven-for-uber-decade-dont-know-what-my-future-holds-2025-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3Eride-hailing%20driver%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%20who%20lives%20in%20Colorado%20and%20drives%20for%20The%20Drivers%20Cooperative%20Colorado%2C%20a%20driver-owned%20ride-hailing%20service.%20It%20has%20about%201%2C500%20drivers%20and%20offers%20rides%20in%20the%20Denver%20area%2C%20Boulder%2C%20Colorado%20Springs%2C%20and%20Fort%20Collins.%20The%20interview%20has%20been%20edited%20for%20length%20and%20clarity.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20bulk%20of%20my%20career%20has%20been%20in%20the%20nonprofit%20sector%2C%20particularly%20in%20development%20and%20fundraising.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWith%20everything%20happening%20in%20our%20country%2C%20from%20the%20murder%20of%20George%20Floyd%20to%20attacks%20against%20LGBTQ%2B%20people%2C%20I%20thought%20something%20needed%20to%20be%20done%20to%20promote%20nonviolence%2C%20especially%20the%20teachings%20of%20Gandhi%20and%20Dr.%20Martin%20Luther%20King%20Jr.%20So%2C%20in%202024%2C%20I%20got%20some%20colleagues%20together%20and%20went%20from%20a%20full-time%20salary%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fchildcare-costs-cant-afford-work-mom-career-choice-2026-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eno%20income%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20found%20a%20new%20nonprofit%20devoted%20to%20teaching%20nonviolence.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20wife%20is%20employed%2C%20and%20so%20we%20are%20financially%20OK.%20Still%2C%20I%20thought%20that%20I%20could%20use%20some%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmost-lucrative-side-hustles-tried-no-experience-2026-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eside%20income%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20saw%20a%20flyer%20promoting%20the%20co-op%2C%20and%20given%20my%20history%20in%20nonprofits%2C%20I%20loved%20the%20concept.%20It%20seemed%20like%20a%20good%20alternative%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhat-openai-needs-to-do-to-become-for-profit-altman-2024-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Einvestor-focused%20companies%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUnlike%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmedical-student-shares-uber-lyft-side-hustle-gig-work-struggles-2025-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EUber%20or%20Lyft%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20drivers%20own%20the%20co-op%20and%20pay%20a%20fee%20to%20join.%20We%20have%20a%20stake%20in%20the%20organization's%20well-being%20and%20help%20it%20grow%20by%20offering%20excellent%20service%20to%20riders.%20It%20also%20offers%20drivers%20a%20better%20rate%20of%20pay%20than%20they%20can%20get%20through%20the%20other%20apps.%20The%20co-op%20takes%2020%25%20of%20each%20trip%20fare.%20Other%20apps%20take%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhy-uber-upfront-pricing-could-be-key-to-business-turnaround-2025-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Emore%20than%20half%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20some%20fares.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELast%20year%2C%20I%20made%20about%20%245%2C000%20through%20the%20co-op.%20I%20worked%20eight%20to%2010%20hours%20a%20week%20and%20fit%20in%20work%20on%20my%20new%20nonprofit%20in%20between%20rides.%20I%20knew%20that%20the%20co-op%20was%20a%20new%20venture%20%E2%80%94%20we%20launched%20a%20new%20app%20last%20year%20%E2%80%94%20and%20that%20I%20wouldn't%20make%20a%20ton%20of%20money%2C%20but%20I%20was%20cool%20with%20that.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22f060c20f-6d5b-4445-bf36-61f67876636a%5C%22%3EThe%20drivers'%20co-op%20is%20a%20work%20in%20progress%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWe're%20still%20building%20both%20the%20rider%20and%20driver%20bases%20in%20some%20areas.%20I%20live%20on%20the%20west%20side%20of%20the%20Denver%20Metro%20area%2C%20and%20rides%20out%20here%20on%20the%20app%20are%20limited.%20As%20a%20result%2C%20I%20drive%20a%20few%20miles%20south%20to%20a%20busier%20area%20where%20I%20can%20park%20and%20serve%20more%20people.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20a%20Friday%20or%20Saturday%20night%2C%20I%20might%20take%20a%20ride%20from%20my%20suburb%20into%20Denver.%20That%20gives%20me%20the%20opportunity%20to%20hang%20out%20in%20the%20central%20part%20of%20town%2C%20pick%20up%20rides%20for%20a%20few%20hours%2C%20then%20call%20it%20a%20day%20and%20go%20home.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20feels%20like%20there's%20also%20a%20stronger%20community%20through%20the%20co-op.%20I'm%20getting%20to%20meet%20other%20drivers%20from%20other%20countries%C2%A0during%20the%20co-op%20meetings.%20We%20have%20gotten%20to%20know%20each%20other%2C%20and%20we%20watch%20out%20for%20each%20other.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20believe%20the%20economy%20is%20for%20people%2C%20and%20that%20people%20should%20not%20be%20treated%20as%20mere%20cogs%20for%20the%20benefit%20of%20company%20owners.%20With%20the%20co-op%2C%20there's%20dignity%20in%20work%2C%20and%20we're%20honoring%20each%20other's%20work%20as%20we%20build%20this%20app%20together.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EDo%20you%20have%20a%20story%20to%20share%20about%20Uber%2C%20DoorDash%2C%20or%20another%20gig%20app%3F%20Contact%20this%20reporter%20at%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22mailto%3Aabitter%40businessinsider.com%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cu%3Eabitter%40businessinsider.com%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%20or%20via%20encrypted%20messaging%20app%20Signal%20at%20808-854-4501.%20Use%20a%20personal%20email%20address%2C%20a%20nonwork%20WiFi%20network%2C%20and%20a%20nonwork%20device%3B%20%3C%2Fem%3Ehere's%20our%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Finsider-guide-to-securely-sharing-whistleblower-information-about-powerful-institutions-2021-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_self%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cu%3Eguide%20to%20sharing%20information%20securely%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgig-worker-chose-cooperative-over-uber-lyft-side-money-2026-4%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1777195981000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69dffbf716ad6f0000dc4e5d%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgig-worker-chose-cooperative-over-uber-lyft-side-money-2026-4%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Daniel%20Mondragon%20works%20for%20a%20ride-hailing%20cooperative%20in%20Colorado.%20The%20driver-owned%20service%20helps%20him%20make%20money%20as%20he%20starts%20his%20own%20nonprofit.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22abitter%40businessinsider.com%20(Alex%20Bitter)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22I%20paid%20my%20customers%20back%20for%20tariffs.%20My%20business%20has%20been%20on%20the%20phone%20with%20Customs%20trying%20to%20get%20our%20refund.%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221666%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Dame%20co-founder%20Alexandra%20Fine%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69eb9bf73fecbb42897a3c44%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221250%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EAlexandra%20Fine%2C%20cofounder%20of%20Dame%2C%20a%20sexual%20wellness%20brand.%3Cp%3EDame%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EDame%20Products%20cofounder%20Alexandra%20Fine%20added%20a%20Trump%20surcharge%20last%20year%20for%20tariff%20costs.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EIn%202026%2C%20she%20reimbursed%20customers%20for%20the%20fees%20after%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20ruled%20against%20many%20of%20Trump's%20tariffs.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EHer%20business%20is%20pursuing%20its%20own%20refund%20through%20the%20US%20Customs%20portal%2C%20which%20opened%20in%20April.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20as-told-to%20essay%20is%20based%20on%20a%20conversation%20with%20Alexandra%20Fine%2C%20cofounder%20of%20Dame%20Products%2C%20a%20sexual%20wellness%20brand%20that%20was%20affected%20by%20Trump's%20tariff%20policies.%20US%20Customs%20and%20Border%20Protection%20opened%20a%20refund%20portal%20on%20Monday%2C%20allowing%20importers%20to%20file%20for%20tariff%20refunds.%20The%20interview%20has%20been%20edited%20for%20length%20and%20clarity.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20cofounder%2C%20Janet%20Lieberman%2C%20and%20I%20started%20Dame%20in%202014%20as%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwomen-sexual-wellness-startup-dame-raises-series-a-funding-2022-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efemale-founded%20vibrator%20brand%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20launched%20a%20funding%20campaign%20on%20Indiegogo%2C%20raising%20%24575%2C000%20in%2045%20days%2C%20and%20have%20since%20grown%20the%20business.%20We%20sell%20directly%20on%20our%20website%20and%20at%20major%20retailers%20like%20Walmart%20and%20Target.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPart%20of%20our%20supply%20chain%20was%20in%20the%20US%20at%20first%2C%20but%20it%20was%20very%20expensive%20because%20we%20shipped%20everything%20to%20China%20for%20final%20assembly%2C%20and%20tariffs%20on%20imports%20from%20China%20were%20really%20high.%20China%20is%20excellent%20at%20making%20silicon%20molds%2C%20which%20are%20a%20really%20important%20part%20of%20how%20we%20make%20vibrators%20and%20are%20hard%20to%20find%20anywhere%20else%2C%20so%20we%20moved%20all%20production%20there.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20tariffs%20started%20increasing%20last%20year%2C%20some%20of%20my%20founder%20friends%20were%20able%20to%20source%20materials%20from%20Vietnam%20or%20Mexico%2C%20but%20shifting%20production%20wasn't%20a%20practical%20option%20for%20us.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%228c16a0fe-f0e1-43dd-96f4-fee9d7d7945c%5C%22%3EThe%20post-Liberation%20Day%20scramble%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20Liberation%20Day%2C%20when%20Trump%20held%20up%20the%20sign%20with%20all%20the%20tariff%20rates%2C%20we%20were%20scrambling.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20had%20inventory%20coming%20in%20that%20was%20suddenly%20going%20to%20cost%20us%2050%25%20more%20than%20we%20thought.%20We%20had%20to%20redo%20our%20inventory%20forecasting%2C%20and%20that%20took%20time.%20Then%2C%20two%20days%20later%2C%20the%20tariffs%20went%20up%20again.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20high%20costs%20meant%20we%20had%20some%20weeks%20when%20we%20were%20out%20of%20stock%20and%20lost%20out%20on%20possible%20sales.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20a%20nightmare%20and%20stressful%20for%20my%20relationships%20with%20Target%2C%20Walmart%2C%20and%20the%20other%20retailers%20I%20sell%20to.%20Many%20companies%20require%2090%20days%20to%20change%20prices%2C%20so%20we%20couldn't%20quickly%20adjust%20to%20offset%20our%20higher%20costs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20ended%20up%20adding%20a%20Trump%20tariff%20surcharge%20to%20orders%20on%20our%20website%2C%20which%20was%20kind%20of%20a%20consumer%20education%20marketing%20campaign%20for%20us.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20concept%20got%20us%20publicity%2C%20but%20ultimately%20led%20to%20huge%20cart%20abandonment.%20It%20turns%20out%20folks%20don't%20like%20getting%20to%20checkout%20to%20find%20they're%20being%20charged%20more%20for%20the%20product%20than%20they%20thought%20they'd%20be%2C%20which%20was%20our%20whole%20point%20because%20that%20was%20our%20experience%20with%20tariffs.%20The%20%245%20to%20%2415%20we%20were%20charging%20also%20wasn't%20enough%20to%20fully%20cover%20the%20tariffs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20about%20two%20weeks%2C%20we%20made%20an%20update%20so%20customers%20would%20see%20the%20charge%2C%20but%20it%20would%20be%20crossed%20out%2C%20meaning%20they%20wouldn't%20have%20to%20pay%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20think%2C%20had%20we%20raised%20our%20prices%2C%20we%20wouldn't%20have%20seen%20so%20much%20cart%20abandonment%20because%20most%20people%20wouldn't%20have%20realized%20the%20prices%20were%20higher.%20But%20we%20really%20wanted%20to%20call%20it%20out.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2287f5e942-9e6b-4f6e-9c3f-0b44c4a2200e%5C%22%3EWe%20made%20up%20our%20minds%20early%20to%20repay%20the%20surcharge%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20we%20waited%20for%20a%20Supreme%20Court%20decision%20on%20tariffs%20earlier%20this%20year%2C%20we%20assumed%20that%20if%20they%20were%20overturned%2C%20there%20would%20be%20a%20refund.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESo%20we%20planned%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-fedex-ups-dhl-plan-to-refund-customers-for-tariffs-2026-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eautomatically%20repay%20everyone%3C%2Fa%3E%20who%20had%20paid%20us%20for%20the%20Trump%20surcharge.%20It%20wasn't%20a%20huge%20amount%20anyway%20%E2%80%94%20we%20gave%20back%20less%20than%20%2410%2C000%20altogether%20within%20a%20few%20weeks%20of%20the%20court%20decision.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20don't%20know%20if%20people%20really%20noticed%20the%20refund.%20We%20don't%20show%20up%20as%20Dame%20Products%2C%20a%20sex%20toy%20company%2C%20on%20a%20credit%20card%20bill.%20We%20are%20more%20discreet%20on%20your%20statement%2C%20so%20I%20wonder%20if%20people%20who%20didn't%20catch%20the%20email%20saw%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStill%2C%20the%20people%20who%20did%20notice%20it%20and%20saw%20the%20messaging%20were%20really%20positive.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBecause%20we%20charged%20the%20fee%20separately%2C%20it%20was%20easy%20for%20us%20to%20automatically%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcostco-member-sues-for-share-of-tariffs-refund-2026-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Egive%20people%20the%20money%20back%3C%2Fa%3E.%20It%20made%20us%20ask%2C%20why%20can't%20the%20government%20make%20its%20system%20automatic%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe're%20looking%20to%20get%20a%20%2490%2C000%20refund%20for%20our%20business%2C%20and%20so%20far%2C%20the%20rebate%20process%20with%20Customs%20has%20been%20frustrating.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2247882256-9a49-424a-af66-13a0bd18e108%5C%22%3EOur%20refund%20process%20is%20off%20to%20a%20rocky%20start%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ERight%20now%2C%20we're%20having%20trouble%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fieepa-tariff-refund-portal-tops-26000-sign-ups-166-billion-2026-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Elogging%20in%20to%20the%20portal%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20is%20the%20first%20step%20to%20making%20a%20claim.%20Our%20customs%20broker%20uses%20this%20portal%20all%20the%20time%2C%20but%20we%20haven't%20logged%20in%20over%20five%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20tried%20calling%20tech%20support%2C%20and%20our%20operations%20person%20was%20on%20hold%20for%20over%20five%20hours%20on%20Wednesday%20before%20being%20disconnected.%20The%20day%20before%20that%2C%20it%20was%20three%20and%20a%20half%20hours%2C%20and%20then%20they%20disconnected%20her.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFinally%2C%20at%202%3A30%20a.m%20on%20Friday%2C%20she%20got%20a%20call%20back.%20It%20didn't%20fix%20the%20issue%2C%20but%20it's%20progress.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe're%20a%20really%20small%20team%2C%20so%20%2490%2C000%20is%20a%20huge%20amount%20for%20us.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20had%20been%20working%20on%20reducing%20our%20overhead%20before%20the%20tariffs%20hit%2C%20but%20they%20basically%20wiped%20out%20that%20progress.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe're%20not%20stopping%2C%20though%2C%20because%20I%20really%20believe%20in%20what%20we're%20doing%2C%20and%20I%20think%20that%20the%20offering%20we%20make%20matters%20in%20the%20world%20to%20improve%20sexual%20well-being%20for%20women.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EEditor's%20note%3A%20A%20US%20Customs%20spokesperson%20did%20not%20immediately%20have%20a%20comment%20on%20the%20login%20issue%2C%20but%20said%20they%20were%20looking%20into%20it.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EHave%20a%20tip%3F%20Contact%20this%20reporter%20via%20email%20at%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22mailto%3Adreuter%40businessinsider.com%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3Edreuter%40businessinsider.com%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%20or%20text%2Fcall%2FSignal%20at%20646-768-4750%3C%2Fem%3E.%20%3Cem%3EUse%20a%20personal%20email%20address%2C%20a%20nonwork%20WiFi%20network%2C%20and%20a%20nonwork%20device%3B%20here's%20our%20guide%20to%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Finsider-guide-to-securely-sharing-whistleblower-information-about-powerful-institutions-2021-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3Esharing%20information%20securely%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdame-founder-tackles-tariff-repayment-navigating-the-refund-process-2026-4%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1777195741000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69eb9c0c3fecbb42897a3c47%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdame-founder-tackles-tariff-repayment-navigating-the-refund-process-2026-4%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Dame%20cofounder%20Alexandra%20Fine%20describes%20how%20she%20repaid%20customers%20for%20the%20Trump%20tariff%20surcharge%20and%20is%20seeking%20a%20refund%20for%20her%20business.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22dreuter%40businessinsider.com%20(Dominick%20Reuter)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Buying%20an%20apartment%20seemed%20my%20best%20option.%20Visiting%20a%20tiny%20home%20village%20showed%20me%20another%20way%20to%20live.%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EThe%20offers%20and%20details%20on%20this%20page%20may%20have%20updated%20or%20changed%20since%20the%20time%20of%20publication.%20See%20our%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhy-visiting-a-tiny-home-village-made-me-rethink-homeownership-2026-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20current%20information.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223543%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Tiny%20home%20village%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69b4302c4d65ec517529f81e%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222866%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThere%20are%20Minitopia%20villages%20across%20the%20North%20Brabant%20region%20of%20the%20Netherlands.%3Cp%3ESamira%20Kafala%20for%20BI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EFive%20years%20ago%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Finheritance-how-spent-saved-invested-110000-2025-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EI%20used%20a%20small%20inheritance%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20the%20savings%20from%20moving%20back%20in%20with%20my%20parents%20to%20buy%20a%20modest%20apartment%20in%20the%20suburbs%20of%20London.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20extremely%20dated%3A%20popcorn%20walls%2C%20threadbare%20carpet%2C%20a%20full-blown%201970s%20time%20capsule.%20I%20drained%20most%20of%20my%20savings%20on%20the%20deposit%20and%20spent%20what%20little%20remained%20on%20the%20renovation%2C%20but%20I%20was%20thrilled%20to%20have%20achieved%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fzillennial-lives-with-parents-spends-on-luxury-goods-2023-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ethe%20zillennial%20dream%3A%3C%2Fa%3E%20homeownership.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENow%2C%20roughly%2030%25%20of%20my%20salary%20goes%20toward%20the%20mortgage.%20In%20a%20good%20month%2C%20I%20can%20save%20about%20a%20third%20of%20my%20income.%20I%20know%20I'm%20one%20of%20the%20lucky%20ones.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fborn-in-nineties-feel-stuck-between-two-genereations-2024-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EAs%20a%20zillennial%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20too%20old%20for%20Gen%20Z%2C%20too%20young%20to%20count%20as%20millennials%20%E2%80%94%20we%20exist%20in%20a%20generational%20limbo.%20When%20it%20comes%20to%20housing%2C%20many%20in%20my%20cohort%20feel%20too%20grown%20up%20to%20clean%20up%20after%20strangers%20in%20a%20shared%20apartment%2C%20and%20yet%20too%20poor%20to%20buy%20the%20kind%20of%20detached%20homes%20our%20parents%20bought%20for%20a%20fraction%20of%20their%20income.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20was%20under%20the%20illusion%20that%20my%20only%20three%20options%20were%20to%20share%2C%20rent%2C%20or%20stretch%20to%20afford%20a%20traditional%20home%20%E2%80%94%20a%20choice%20between%20the%20undignified%20and%20the%20unattainable.%20What%20I%20had%20failed%20to%20consider%20was%20a%20fourth%20option.%20A%20tinier%20one.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Caside%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBusiness%20Insider's%20Joshua%20Nelken-Zitser%20spent%20several%20nights%20in%20Minitopia%2C%20a%20tiny%20home%20village%20in%20the%20Netherlands.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20story%20is%20part%20of%20his%20series%20exploring%20how%20living%20in%20the%20villages%20has%20affected%20residents'%20careers%2C%20lives%2C%20and%20finances.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3C%2Faside%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20mid-February%2C%20I%20found%20myself%20on%20a%20reporting%20trip%20in%20North%20Brabant%2C%20in%20the%20south%20of%20the%20Netherlands%2C%20visiting%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwant-to-live-in-europe-retire-tiny-home-netherlands-2026-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ea%20cluster%20of%20tiny-home%20villages%3C%2Fa%3E%20run%20by%20the%20Minitopia%20Foundation.%20It%20was%20launched%20a%20decade%20ago%20on%20a%20simple%20premise%3A%20secure%20leases%20on%20derelict%20land%2C%20divide%20the%20land%20into%20plots%2C%20and%20then%20rent%20out%20those%20plots%20to%20people%20for%20a%20few%20hundred%20euros%20a%20month%20to%20build%20a%20tiny%20home%20on.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223543%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22tiny%20home%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69eb7c69367066d7c29708f0%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222525%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EMany%20of%20the%20tiny%20homes%20at%20Minitopia%20sites%20are%20built%20by%20their%20owners.%3Cp%3ESamira%20Kafala%20for%20BI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20began%20in%20's-Hertogenbosch%2C%20the%20province's%20capital%2C%20where%20Minitopia's%20first%20residents%20constructed%20houses%20for%20as%20little%20as%20%E2%82%AC5%2C000.%20Nowadays%2C%20there%20are%20five%20Minitopia%20sites%20across%20the%20region%2C%20with%20more%20than%20150%20plots%2C%20and%20the%20foundation%20says%20there%20are%20around%202%2C000%20people%20on%20the%20waiting%20list.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOther%20countries%2C%20including%20the%20US%20and%20the%20UK%2C%20have%20experimented%20with%20similar%2C%20smaller%20communities%20of%20tiny%20homes.%20Business%20leaders%20have%20also%20envisioned%20this%20style%20of%20living%20as%20a%20solution%3B%20Tony%20Hsieh%2C%20who%20died%20in%202020%2C%20had%20planned%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftony-hsieh-las-vegas-trailer-park-2017-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Erevamp%20Las%20Vegas%20%3C%2Fa%3Ethrough%20a%20trailer-park%20tiny-home%20community.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20many%20of%20these%20existing%20communities%20are%20rural%20or%20on%20the%20outskirts%20of%20small%20towns%2C%20Minitopia%20is%20an%20experimental%20attempt%20to%20solve%20a%20distinctly%20urban%20problem%3A%20how%20to%20live%20affordably%20in%20a%20city.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223543%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Tiny%20home%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69eb7c16a98bc8fdc096e5f8%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222657%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ERolf%20van%20Boxmeer%20co-founded%20the%20Minitopia%20Foundation%20in%202016.%3Cp%3ESamira%20Kafala%20for%20BI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EI%20arrived%20at%20Eindhoven%20Airport%2C%20bleary-eyed%20after%20an%20early%20departure%20from%20London%2C%20to%20meet%20the%20person%20who%20would%20be%20my%20guide%20for%20most%20of%20the%20trip.%20Jos%20van%20der%20Muelen%2C%2029%2C%20works%20for%20Minitopia%20and%20has%20also%20been%20a%20resident%20at%20the%20Eindhoven%20site%20%E2%80%94%20the%20biggest%20of%20Minitopia's%20five%20sites%20%E2%80%94%20for%20the%20past%20two%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIn%20London%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20asked%20as%20we%20pulled%20away%20from%20the%20airport%20in%20his%20truck%2C%20%26quot%3Bdo%20you%20live%20in%20a%20big%20house%3F%26quot%3B%20I%20laughed.%20%26quot%3BNo%2C%20an%20apartment%2C%26quot%3B%20I%20responded.%20For%20most%20people%20my%20age%2C%20a%20big%20house%20in%20the%20city%20is%20little%20more%20than%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmillennial-bought-more-expensive-dream-home-sometimes-wishes-still-rented-2024-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ea%20pipe%20dream.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20latest%20Office%20for%20National%20Statistics%20data%20shows%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffirst-time-homeowner-london-wasnt-prepared-for-depression-2024-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ea%20London%20home%3C%2Fa%3E%20costs%20roughly%2011%20times%20the%20median%20salary.%20Renting%20a%20place%20of%20your%20own%20isn't%20much%20more%20affordable.%20The%20inequality%20nonprofit%20Trust%20for%20London%20estimates%20that%2053%25%20of%20the%20average%20pre-tax%20income%20is%20needed%20to%20afford%20a%20one-bedroom%20flat%20in%20the%20capital.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20a%20similar%20tale%20in%20the%20Netherlands%2C%20van%20der%20Muelen%20told%20me.%20Many%20of%20his%20friends%20still%20live%20with%20their%20parents%2C%20priced%20out%20of%20both%20buying%20and%20renting%2C%20left%20saving%20up%20for%20years%20in%20the%20hope%20of%20one%20day%20making%20it%20onto%20the%20housing%20ladder.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20country%20is%20short%20roughly%20410%2C000%20homes%2C%20placing%20it%20among%20Europe's%20more%20housing-scarce%20countries%2C%20according%20to%20the%20Dutch%20banking%20group%20ING.%20Low%20supply%20and%20high%20demand%20have%20driven%20a%20housing%20affordability%20crisis%2C%20which%20became%20a%20central%20issue%20in%20the%202025%20general%20election.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20Eindhoven%20region%2C%20the%20average%20house%20price%20was%20about%20%E2%82%AC470%2C000%20at%20the%20end%20of%202025%2C%20while%20average%20annual%20income%20was%20roughly%20%E2%82%AC43%2C700%2C%20making%20homeownership%20equally%20as%20unaffordable%20as%20in%20London.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20truck%20pulled%20into%20the%20Minitopia%20site%20in%20Eindhoven.%20A%20patchwork%20of%20houses%20stretched%20out%20before%20us.%20A%20few%20looked%20sleek%20and%20modern%3B%20others%20felt%20improvised%2C%20almost%20ramshackle.%20One%20or%20two%20were%20no%20bigger%20than%20a%20garden%20shed%2C%20but%20many%20were%20two-stories%20high%20and%20not%20that%20tiny%20at%20all.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20we%20walked%20around%20the%20grounds%2C%20I%20met%20one%20of%20its%20residents.%20Margot%20Hollander%2C%20a%20glamorous%2064-year-old%20retired%20dance%20teacher%20with%20a%20neat%20blonde%20bob%2C%20welcomed%20me%20into%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbought-tiny-home-after-divorce-gave-fresh-start-afford-2026-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eher%20tiny%20home.%3C%2Fa%3E%20She%20bought%20it%20in%202024%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftiny-home-villages-older-divorced-women-over-50-minitopia-2026-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ecash%20after%20her%20divorce%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20using%20about%20%24143%2C000%20from%20the%20settlement.%20The%20space%20is%20compact%20but%20chic%2C%20decked%20out%20in%20minimalist%20Scandinavian-style%20furniture.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223300%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Margot%20Hollander%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69ce824ee762ed6cfe4499c5%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%224134%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EMargot%20Hollander%2C%2064%2C%20bought%20her%20tiny%20home%20in%202024.%3Cp%3ESamira%20Kafala%20for%20BI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20the%20simple%20things%2C%20like%20making%20small%20talk%20on%20the%20way%20to%20the%20parking%20lot%2C%20that%20give%20me%20such%20a%20good%20feeling%20about%20living%20here%2C%26quot%3B%20Hollander%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFrom%20the%20village-like%20feel%20of%20Minitopia%2C%20you%20wouldn't%20know%20it's%20only%20four%20miles%20from%20central%20Eindhoven%2C%20the%20Netherlands'%20technological%20hub%2C%20which%20locals%20call%20the%20%26quot%3BDutch%20Silicon%20Valley.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22291a5ea1-b4a9-474b-bcc0-eff2b5321511%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EMy%20night%20in%20a%20tiny%20home%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20reached%20van%20der%20Muelen's%20timber-clad%2C%20two-story%20house%2C%20which%20he%20built%20himself.%20Inside%2C%20I%20found%20a%20spacious%20living%20room%20with%20high%20ceilings%20and%20natural%20light.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20home%20is%20at%20the%20upper%20end%20of%20what%20Minitopia%20considers%20a%20tiny%20house.%20For%20%26quot%3Bhardcore%2C%20tiny-house%20believers%2C%26quot%3B%20Minitopia%20cofounder%20Rolf%20van%20Boxmeer%20told%20me%2C%20around%20320%20square%20feet%20is%20the%20maximum%20to%20qualify%20under%20the%20definition.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222831%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Tiny%20home%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69c59a78b87081653c9a65db%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223543%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20typical%20tiny%20home%20maxes%20out%20at%20320%20square%20feet.%3Cp%3ESamira%20Kafala%20for%20BI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20540%20square%20feet%2C%20van%20der%20Muelen's%20tiny%20home%20is%20exactly%20the%20same%20size%20as%20my%20London%20apartment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20would%20be%20spending%20the%20night%20in%20van%20der%20Muelen's%20place.%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EI%20had%20braced%20for%20claustrophobia%2C%20imagining%20something%20close%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcapsule-hotel-review-photos-bangkok-airport-great-value-2025-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ea%20capsule%20hotel.%3C%2Fa%3E%20In%20reality%2C%20there%20was%20plenty%20of%20space%20to%20move%20around.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20stepped%20into%20the%20garden%20and%20felt%20a%20flicker%20of%20envy.%20I%20have%20no%20outdoor%20space%20at%20home%2C%20and%20few%20of%20my%20friends%20in%20London%20do%20either.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20morning%2C%20after%20a%20solid%20night's%20sleep%2C%20van%20der%20Muelen%20returned%20to%20his%20home%20with%20his%20wife%2C%20Fenna%20Wit%2C%20and%20their%20children%2C%20aged%201%20and%203.%20Wit%20headed%20upstairs%20to%20take%20a%20call%20in%20the%20small%20area%20they%20have%20set%20aside%20for%20working%20from%20home%2C%20while%20van%20der%20Muelen%20hooked%20a%20swing%20onto%20the%20doorframe%20for%20the%20eldest%20child%20to%20play%20on.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20house%20has%20been%20designed%20around%20their%20needs.%20The%20kitchen%20is%20compact%20%E2%80%94%20they%20don't%20cook%20much%20%E2%80%94%20and%20they%20have%20prioritized%20space%20for%20a%20bath%20and%20for%20the%20kids%20to%20play.%20It%20will%20be%20tight%20when%20the%20children%20are%20older%2C%20van%20der%20Muelen%20admitted%2C%20but%20for%20now%2C%20it%20works%20just%20fine.%20They%20can%20always%20build%20an%20extension%2C%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222718%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Family%20in%20tiny%20house.%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69c59a09b87081653c9a65d5%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223543%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EJos%20van%20der%20Muelen%20and%20Fenna%20Wit%20live%20in%20a%20tiny%20home%20with%20their%20two%20toddler-aged%20children.%3Cp%3ESamira%20Kafala%20for%20BI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20homes%20are%20technically%20classified%20as%20temporary%2C%20meaning%20traditional%20mortgages%20aren't%20available.%20As%20a%20result%2C%20construction%20costs%20must%20be%20paid%20up%20front.%20It%20cost%20van%20der%20Muelen%20and%20Wit%20about%20%E2%82%AC75%2C000%20to%20build%20theirs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20plots%20are%20also%20leased%20rather%20than%20owned%2C%20meaning%20residents%20may%20eventually%20need%20to%20dismantle%20and%20relocate%2C%20which%20several%20residents%20told%20me%20is%20one%20of%20the%20model's%20key%20drawbacks.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20this%20family%2C%20however%2C%20any%20downsides%20feel%20worth%20it%20for%20now.%20Their%20monthly%20housing%20costs%2C%20including%20ground%20rent%2C%20utilities%2C%20and%20insurance%2C%20account%20for%20about%2010%25%20of%20their%20joint%20income.%20They%20are%20typically%20able%20to%20save%20almost%2060%25%20of%20their%20salaries.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20low%20costs%20give%20them%20some%20financial%20and%20professional%20freedom%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffamily-toddlers-tiny-home-3-day-week-saves-income-2026-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EBoth%20now%20work%20three%20days%3C%2Fa%3E%20a%20week.%20%26quot%3BWe%20both%20work%20now%2C%20just%20because%20we%20want%20to%20and%20not%20because%20we%20need%20to%2C%26quot%3B%20Wit%20said.%20%26quot%3BWe%20have%20a%20lot%20of%20days%20at%20home%20with%20the%20kids.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22b7b3e2ee-5c6e-4944-86f6-f06b1a0ab4a7%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EI%20was%20starting%20to%20become%20a%20tiny-home%20believer%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EOver%20the%20following%20days%2C%20I%20met%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fminitopia-move-tiny-home-village-son-safe-free-raise-children-2026-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eother%20Minitopia%20residents%3C%2Fa%3E%20who%20told%20me%20similar%20stories%20of%20tiny%20homes%20bringing%20a%20sense%20of%20financial%20security.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EVan%20der%20Muelen%20and%20Wit's%20neighbors%2C%20Nico%20and%20Margareth%20Bluigmars%2C%20both%20in%20their%2060s%2C%20enthused%20about%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcouple-60s-built-tiny-home-mortgage-free-pros-cons-2026-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ejoys%20of%20living%20mortgage-free.%3C%2Fa%3E%20%26quot%3BFor%20me%2C%20being%20mortgage-free%20has%20made%20me%20feel%20much%20more%20relaxed%2C%26quot%3B%20Margareth%20told%20me%20from%20inside%20their%20cozy%20home%2C%20decorated%20with%20stained%20glass%20lamps%20she'd%20designed%20in%20her%20studio.%20They%20built%20the%20tiny%20house%20using%20the%20money%20from%20the%20sale%20of%20their%20family%20home.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223543%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Nico%20Bluigmars%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69a70942fd4fbd083f296b7e%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222831%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ENico%20Bluigmars%2C%2064%2C%20built%20his%20own%20tiny%20home%20in%20Eindhoven.%3Cp%3ESamira%20Kafala%20for%20BI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EAnne%20Leijdekkers%20and%20Simone%20Solazzo%2C%20a%20couple%20in%20their%2030s%20who%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcouple-tiny-home-pitch-deck-win-over-sceptical-parents-2026-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Elive%20in%20the%20Minitopia%20site%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20Valkenswaard%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbuilt-tiny-home-house-using-chatgpt-ai-useful-guidance-was-2026-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ebuilt%20their%20tiny%20home%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20about%20%E2%82%AC75%2C000.%20%26quot%3BWe%20don't%20have%20a%20mortgage%2C%20and%20our%20monthly%20costs%20are%20relatively%20low%2C%26quot%3B%20Solazzo%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20my%20time%20in%20the%20Netherlands%20came%20to%20a%20close%2C%20I%20found%20myself%20comparing%20lives%20with%20my%20Minitopia%20guide.%20Van%20der%20Muelen's%20version%20of%20nearly-30%20looked%20very%20different%20from%20mine.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20had%20built%20a%20home%20in%20the%20city%20that%20allowed%20him%20to%20work%20less%20and%20save%20more%2C%20while%20I%20still%20work%20five%20days%20a%20week%20and%20spend%20about%2030%25%20of%20my%20income%20on%20my%20apartment.%20This%20falls%20within%20the%20range%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhalf-american-renters-ignore-key-financial-rule-on-housing-spending-2024-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Erecommended%20by%20personal%20finance%20experts%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20housing%20costs%2C%20but%20it's%20still%20a%20huge%20part%20of%20my%20monthly%20budget.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223543%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Tiny%20home%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22http