t%20I%20was%20surprised%20when%20the%20news%20came.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202021%2C%20I%20started%20working%20as%20a%20technician%20for%20Intel%2C%20based%20in%20Hillsboro%2C%20Oregon.%20I%20was%2059%20at%20the%20time%2C%20and%20I%20remember%20thinking%3A%20%26quot%3BWhy%20are%20you%20hiring%20some%20old%20fart%20like%20me%3F%26quot%3B%20Over%20the%20next%20few%20years%2C%20I%20survived%20multiple%20rounds%20of%20layoffs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThen%2C%20in%20March%202025%2C%20Intel%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fintel-new-ceo-wants-customer-feedback-turnaround-lip-bu-tan-2025-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ebrought%20on%20a%20new%20CEO%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20it%20seemed%20like%20there%20was%20more%20of%20an%20emphasis%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbig-tech-flattening-middle-managers-performance-efficiency-ai-2025-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ereducing%20management%20layers%3C%2Fa%3E.%20I%20figured%2C%20%26quot%3BWell%2C%20I'm%20not%20a%20manager%2C%20so%20I%20should%20be%20safe.%26quot%3B%20I%20thought%20I'd%20retire%20there%2C%20but%20I%20was%20wrong.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20July%207%2C%20I%20learned%20that%20I'd%20been%20laid%20off%20%E2%80%94%20and%20my%20last%20day%20of%20employment%20was%20July%2031.%20Since%20then%2C%20I've%20been%20struggling%20to%20find%20work%2C%20and%20retirement%20isn't%20feasible%20for%20me%20right%20now.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2280e74d30-995f-4654-abe4-6df2542822e4%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EI%20took%20some%20time%20off%20before%20job%20hunting%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20layoff%20hurt%20because%20I%20worked%20really%20hard%20for%20the%20company%20and%20really%20liked%20the%20job.%20I%20didn't%20start%20looking%20for%20work%20right%20away.%20I%20had%20some%20savings%2C%20several%20weeks%20of%20severance%20pay%2C%20and%20I%20knew%20I%20could%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fjob-seeker-recession-hiring-labor-market-unemployed-americans-federal-government-2026-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ecollect%20unemployment%20benefits%3C%2Fa%3E.%20This%20bought%20me%20some%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20of%20the%20first%20things%20I%20did%20was%20take%20a%20monthlong%20road%20trip%20to%20Colorado%2C%20but%20I%20wasn't%20there%20just%20for%20a%20vacation.%20I%20took%20a%20multi-week%20class%20on%20electric%20vehicle%20charger%20maintenance%20through%20a%20free%20program%20organized%20by%20Goodwill.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20thought%20process%20was%3A%20The%20class%20is%20free%2C%20I've%20never%20been%20to%20Colorado%2C%20I%20have%20an%20interest%20in%20electric%20vehicles%2C%20and%20it%20might%20help%20me%20find%20a%20new%20job.%20I%20knew%20the%20Oregon%20state%20government%20had%20plans%20to%20add%20more%20EV%20chargers%20across%20the%20state%2C%20so%20I%20thought%20it%20could%20be%20a%20lucrative%20area%20to%20get%20into.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20the%20class%2C%20I%20decided%20to%20extend%20my%20break%20from%20the%20working%20world%2C%20spending%20about%20a%20month%20in%20California%20for%20what%20I%20thought%20of%20as%20a%20post-layoff%20trip.%20I%20still%20had%20some%20savings%20and%20hadn't%20started%20collecting%20unemployment%20benefits%20yet.%20From%20what%20I%20understood%2C%20I%20wasn't%20eligible%20for%20unemployment%20if%20I%20wasn't%20in%20the%20state.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAround%20last%20November%2C%20I%20started%20collecting%20unemployment%20and%20actively%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Funemployed-months-grad-school-middle-age-2026-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Elooking%20for%20work%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20LinkedIn%20and%20Indeed%2C%20including%20for%20semiconductor%20specialist%20roles.%20I%20tried%20tapping%20into%20my%20Intel%20network%20for%20opportunities%2C%20but%20nothing%20came%20of%20that.%20While%20I've%20landed%20some%20interviews%2C%20I've%20struggled%20to%20land%20an%20offer.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20my%20search%20has%20dragged%20on%2C%20I've%20also%20started%20exploring%20entrepreneurship%20opportunities%20in%20the%20electric%20vehicle%20space.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Caside%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBusiness%20Insider%20is%20speaking%20with%20workers%20who've%20found%20themselves%20at%20a%20corporate%20crossroads%20%E2%80%94%20whether%20due%20to%20a%20layoff%2C%20resignation%2C%20job%20search%2C%20or%20shifting%20workplace%20expectations.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EShare%20your%20story%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20by%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22%20nofollow%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdocs.google.com%2Fforms%2Fd%2Fe%2F1FAIpQLSechTVqVWQve8iqYssNriCXdtwwdgGRixNNZpmslSKBQqIJ8g%2Fviewform%3Fusp%3Dheader%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efilling%20out%20this%20form%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20contacting%20this%20reporter%20via%20email%20at%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22mailto%3Ajzinkula%40businessinsider.com%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ejzinkula%40businessinsider.com%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20or%20via%20Signal%20at%20jzinkula.29.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3C%2Faside%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2261223530-d5d4-477c-acf0-7f416e4ddf6f%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EI'm%20not%20sure%20if%20my%20age%20has%20worked%20against%20me%20in%20my%20job%20search%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20Intel%20hired%20me%20at%20age%2059%2C%20they%20were%20ramping%20up%20hiring%2C%20and%20it%20seemed%20like%20if%20you%20were%20competent%2C%20they'd%20consider%20hiring%20you.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOnce%20I%20got%20to%20Intel%2C%20there%20were%20people%20in%20their%2070s%20still%20working%20there.%20So%20maybe%20age%20is%20less%20of%20an%20issue%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fai-gold-rush-chip-boom-bust-morningstar-2025-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ethe%20semiconductor%20industry%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20think%20the%20bigger%20issue%20is%20that%20there's%20less%20demand%20for%20the%20type%20of%20work%20I%20did%20at%20Intel.%20There%20are%20many%20technicians%20who%20are%20currently%20looking%20for%20work%2C%20whether%20due%20to%20cost-cutting%20or%20other%20factors.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22120c7f48-da1d-43cf-8d70-e9147c02aaf6%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3ERetiring%20doesn't%20make%20sense%20for%20me%20yet%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI've%20thought%20about%20retirement%2C%20but%20the%20biggest%20obstacle%20for%20me%20is%20healthcare.%20I%20can't%20apply%20for%20Medicare%20until%20I'm%2065%2C%20which%20is%20a%20few%20years%20away%2C%20and%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmap-health-insurance-enrollment-dropped-affordable-care-act-subsidies-2026-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAffordable%20Care%20Act%3C%2Fa%3E%20isn't%20as%20helpful%20with%20the%20subsidies%20expiring.%20Having%20a%20job%20provides%20healthcare%20benefits%2C%20so%20it's%20pretty%20crucial%20that%20I%20get%20back%20to%20work.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20could%20also%20use%20a%20bit%20more%20savings%20in%20my%20retirement%20account%2C%20and%20my%20plan%20has%20been%20to%20collect%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Finvesting%2Fwhat-is-social-security%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efull%20Social%20Security%20benefits%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20would%20mean%20working%20until%20age%2067.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20recent%20months%2C%20I've%20tried%20to%20cut%20back%20on%20my%20spending%20%E2%80%94%20specifically%20on%20fancy%20vacations.%20Even%20before%20I%20was%20laid%20off%2C%20I'd%20begun%20cutting%20back%20on%20non-essential%20spending%20because%20I%20sensed%20the%20economy%20could%20be%20headed%20in%20a%20bad%20direction.%20My%20unemployment%20benefits%20have%20helped%20me%20get%20by%2C%20but%20they%20don't%20last%20forever.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22f6bcdd78-306a-40ee-8988-136f4d8c55aa%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EUnemployment%20sucks%2C%20but%20don't%20give%20up%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI've%20been%20through%20all%20kinds%20of%20economic%20upheavals%20and%20downturns%20in%20my%20roughly%2040-year%20career%2C%20including%20multiple%20layoffs.%20During%20the%20Great%20Recession%2C%20I%20had%20a%20long%20unemployment%20stint%20until%20contract%20work%20helped%20me%20get%20back%20on%20my%20feet.%20It%20always%20sucks%20to%20be%20laid%20off.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20top%20advice%20for%20other%20job%20seekers%20is%20don't%20give%20up.%20Tap%20into%20your%20resources%2C%20tap%20into%20your%20network%2C%20don't%20burn%20bridges%20with%20your%20past%20employer%2C%20and%20accept%20that%20you%20might%20not%20get%20the%20same%20pay%20you%20were%20making%20before.%20Yeah%2C%20it%20sucks.%20But%20there%20is%20still%20work%20out%20there.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fintel-employee-laid-off-job-in-sixties-unemployment-semiconductor-oregon-2026-4%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1777194421000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69e8cd58367066d7c296f816%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fintel-employee-laid-off-job-in-sixties-unemployment-semiconductor-oregon-2026-4%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22A%20former%20Intel%20technician%20in%20his%2060s%20shares%20how%20a%20layoff%20upended%20his%20retirement%20plans%20and%20left%20him%20job%20hunting%20for%20healthcare%20and%20stability.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22jzinkula%40insider.com%20(Jacob%20Zinkula)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22No%20hard%20decoupling%3A%20India%20balances%20China%20trade%20with%20export%20push%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1777194418000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-130528940%2Cimgsize-79100.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fbusiness%2Findia-business%2Fno-hard-decoupling-india-balances-china-trade-with-export-push%2Farticleshow%2F130528716.cms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22India%20is%20strategically%20balancing%20its%20trade%20wi