layoffs-jack-dorsey-gratitude-meeting-employee-reaction-ai-integration-2026-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esweeping%20layoffs%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20dressing%20them%20up%20as%20productivity%20gains.%20They're%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpressure-is-ramping-up-in-big-tech-employees-told-bi-how-they-feel-about-it-2025-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eratcheting%20up%20the%20pressure%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20their%20remaining%20teams%2C%20cracking%20down%20on%20dissent%2C%20tracking%20their%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmeta-new-ai-tool-tracks-staff-activity-sparks-concern-2026-4%3Futm_source%3Dcopy-link%26utm_medium%3Dreferral%26utm_campaign%3Dbusiness-headline-graphic%26utm_content%3Dtopbar%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eworkers'%20every%20keystroke%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20pouring%20billions%20into%20the%20all-consuming%20infrastructure%20of%20AI%20projects%20while%20scaling%20back%20their%20investment%20in%20employees.%20%3Cem%3EThis%20is%20the%20new%20reality%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20they%20say.%20%3Cem%3EIf%20you%20don't%20like%20it%2C%20get%20out.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20you%20are%20an%20asshole%20leader%2C%26quot%3B%20Brown%20told%20me%2C%20%26quot%3Byou%20have%20never%20had%20more%20cover%20than%20you%20have%20right%20now%20to%20continue%20that%20behavior%2C%20because%20of%20the%20strong-man%20authoritarianism%20we're%20seeing.%26quot%3B%20The%20author%20and%20researcher%20said%20she%20had%20%26quot%3Bthe%20behavior%20of%20a%20lot%20of%20tech%20leaders%20right%20now%26quot%3B%20in%20mind.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BCourageous%20leaders%20do%20not%20change%20who%20they%20are%20based%20on%20the%20political%20climate%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BThey%20don't%20look%20to%20see%2C%20'Oh%2C%20empathy's%20not%20in%20style%20today%2C%20I%20think%20I'll%20have%20less%20of%20that.'%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BDoes%20that%20bring%20a%20level%20of%20scrutiny%20to%20leaders%20when%20the%20president%20of%20the%20United%20States%20%E2%80%94%20or%20the%20president%20of%20whatever%20country%20they're%20operating%20from%20%E2%80%94%20predominantly%20has%20a%20different%20perspective%3F%20Yeah%2C%20it%20does.%20It%20really%20does.%20But%20zero%20excuses.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBrown%20met%20me%20this%20month%20in%20a%20hotel%20in%20San%20Francisco%2C%20on%20the%20sidelines%20of%20a%20conference%20hosted%20by%20the%20coaching%20platform%20BetterUp.%20It's%20been%2016%20years%20since%20she%20gave%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ted.com%2Ftalks%2Fbrene_brown_the_power_of_vulnerability%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eviral%20TED%20talk%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20her%20research%20on%20shame%20and%20vulnerability%20that's%20probably%20made%20more%20people%20cry%20than%20anything%20else%20on%20the%20internet%20(it%20now%20has%20nearly%20100%20million%20views).%20In%20person%2C%20she%20was%20exactly%20as%20she%20was%20in%20the%20TED%20talk%3A%20warm%20and%20disarming%2C%20rarely%20breaking%20eye%20contact%2C%20and%20quick%20to%20offer%20self-deprecating%20quips%20that%20kept%20me%20laughing%20through%20the%20interview.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESince%20catapulting%20to%20fame%2C%20Brown%20has%20taken%20her%20research%20and%20applied%20it%20to%20the%20workplace%2C%20creating%20a%20leadership%20curriculum%20that%20was%20acquired%20by%20BetterUp.%20Today%2C%20as%20executive%20chair%20of%20the%20Center%20for%20Daring%20Leadership%2C%20she's%20embedded%20inside%20organizations%20such%20as%20power%20management%20giant%20Eaton%20and%20enterprise%20network%20provider%20Lumen%20Technologies.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20asked%20Brown%20what%20she's%20hearing%20right%20now%20from%20the%20CEOs%20she%20works%20with%2C%20and%20she%20emphasized%20the%20instability%20of%20the%20current%20moment.%20Even%20the%20executives%20running%20successful%20businesses%2C%20she%20said%2C%20are%20standing%20atop%20crumbling%20mountains%20%E2%80%94%20crumbling%20because%20of%20forces%20like%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fai-hype-hasnt-changed-work-yet-bosses-employees-2026-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAI%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20changing%20markets%2C%20and%20geopolitics.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BNo%20matter%20what%20past%20accomplishments%20they%20have%2C%20there's%20no%20planting%20a%20flag%20at%20the%20top%20of%20the%20mountain%20and%20saying%2C%20'We%20need%20to%20maintain%20this%20win%2C'%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BIf%20you%20want%20to%20play%20to%20win%2C%20you're%20going%20to%20have%20to%20look%20out%20at%20the%20next%20peak%20and%20make%20a%20jump.%20And%20not%20only%20do%20you%20have%20to%20go%2C%20you%20have%20to%20bring%20everyone%20with%20you.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EYou%20have%20to%20bring%20everyone%20with%20you%3C%2Fem%3E%20was%20the%20message%20Brown%20kept%20returning%20to%20in%20our%20conversation%20%E2%80%94%20a%20message%20repeated%20by%20the%20other%20speakers%20at%20BetterUp's%20conference%20as%20well.%20Inside%20ballrooms%20packed%20with%20a%20crowd%20of%20mostly%20mid-%20to%20senior-level%20HR%20professionals%2C%20that%20idea%20still%20felt%20like%20a%20given.%20Outside%2C%20in%20much%20of%20corporate%20America%2C%20the%20vibe%20is%20very%20different.%20Speaking%20to%20several%20of%20the%20attendees%2C%20I%20got%20the%20sense%20that%20they%20were%20in%20their%20happy%20place%2C%20a%20temporary%20oasis%20%E2%80%94%20even%20if%20they%20knew%20they%20would%20soon%20be%20returning%20to%20an%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcaptialism-sink-or-swim-era-work-2026-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Euglier%20reality%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20has%20grown%20particularly%20bleak%20for%20them%20in%20recent%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20a%20couple%20years%20of%20nudging%20employees%2C%20many%20companies%20have%20lost%20their%20patience.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmeta-google-jpmorgan-make-ai-performance-reviews-goals-raises-promotions-2026-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAI%20use%20has%20become%20mandatory%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20tied%20to%20performance%20reviews%2C%20and%20ominous%20threats%20along%20the%20lines%20of%20%26quot%3BAI%20or%20else%26quot%3B%20are%20everywhere.%20Brown%2C%20though%2C%20holds%20that%20a%20successful%20transition%20requires%20something%20more%20difficult%3A%20fostering%20trust%20among%20employees%20and%20giving%20them%20a%20sense%20of%20agency.%20%26quot%3BWe%20cannot%20feel%20like%20AI%20is%20happening%20%3Cem%3Eto%3C%2Fem%3E%20us%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20told%20me.%20%26quot%3BThere's%20not%20a%20CEO%20alive%20that%20doesn't%20know%20that%20there's%20nothing%20harder%20than%20building%20trust%20on%20teams%20and%20creating%20a%20sense%20of%20agency.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGiven%20the%20magnitude%20of%20the%20shift%20underway%2C%20I%20wondered%20whether%20tech%20CEOs%20have%20grown%20harsh%20in%20recent%20years%20because%20they're%20scared.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWould%20not%20invest%20an%20ounce%20of%20time%20or%20energy%20trying%20to%20diagnose%20their%20behavior%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20told%20me.%20%26quot%3BDon't%20care.%20What's%20driving%20it%20is%20of%20less%20interest%20to%20me%20than%20what%20it's%20creating.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhat%20would%20happen%20if%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Felon-musk-tesla-hardcore-layoffs-report-2024-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EElon%20Musk%3C%2Fa%3E%20went%20through%20her%20program%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BFortunately%2C%20a%20reality%20I%20don't%20have%20to%20contemplate%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20asked%20Brown%20what%20mistakes%20she's%20seeing%20CEOs%20make%20in%20the%20AI%20transition.%20One%20that%20stood%20out%20to%20her%20is%20implementing%20an%20AI%20strategy%20that%20has%20nothing%20to%20do%20with%20their%20business%20goals.%20She%20acted%20out%20how%20that%20looks%3A%20%26quot%3B'Hey%2C%20give%20me%20an%20AI%20strategy.'%20'That%20does%20what%3F'%20'I%20don't%20give%20a%20shit%2C%20just%20give%20it%20to%20me.'%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnother%20mistake%20she%20pointed%20to%20was%20failing%20to%20invest%20in%20employees%2C%20focusing%20all%20the%20attention%20on%20the%20technology%20itself.%20%26quot%3BIn%20the%20end%2C%20it's%20still%20your%20people%20driving%20your%20business%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20Although%2C%20she%20added%3A%20%26quot%3BI%20can%20see%20the%20seduction%20to%20invest%20in%20the%20non-messy%20thing.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDespite%20these%20misgivings%2C%20Brown%20isn't%20anti-AI.%20She's%20built%20her%20own%20AI%20agent%2C%20feeding%20it%20%26quot%3Beverything%20I%20wanted%20it%20to%20know%20about%20me%20and%20how%20I%20wanted%20it%20to%20think%20about%20what%20it%20told%20me.%26quot%3B%20It%20creates%20briefings%20for%20her%20ahead%20of%20meetings%20with%20the%20executives%20she%20advises%20%E2%80%94%20although%20she's%20also%20found%20herself%20peppering%20it%20with%20personal%20questions%20too%2C%20like%20whether%20she%20should%20add%20creatine%20to%20her%20supplement%20stack.%20Laughing%2C%20she%20described%20its%20tendency%20to%20roast%20her.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20not%20sycophantic%20at%20all%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20insisted.%20Recently%2C%20it%20deadpanned%2C%20%26quot%3BHard%20to%20believe%20you're%20a%20social%20scientist%20sometimes.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EToward%20the%20end%20of%20our%20conversation%20that%20largely%20focused%20on%20executives%2C%20I%20asked%20her%20about%20rank-and-file%20employees.%20Many%20of%20the%20white-collar%20workers%20I've%20been%20talking%20to%20are%20wrestling%20with%20a%20confusing%20mix%20of%20feelings%20about%20AI%20%E2%80%94%20thrilled%20with%20the%20ways%20it's%20been%20useful%2C%20and%20terrified%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fworkers-worry-using-ai-will-make-them-replaceable-2026-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ewhat%20it%20means%20for%20their%20jobs%3C%2Fa%3E.%20They're%20not%20sure%20how%20to%20reconcile%20the%20two.%20What%20should%20they%20do%3F%20%26quot%3BThe%20ability%20to%20hold%20this%20tension%20of%20paradox%20is%20an%20absolute%20leadership%20superpower%20moving%20forward%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3B%3Cem%3EI%20love%20this.%20I%20hate%20it.%20I%20can't%20wait%20to%20get%20on%20it%20and%20I'm%20scared%20to%20death%20about%20it.%3C%2Fem%3E%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe's%20hopeful%20but%20also%20fearful%20herself%20%E2%80%94%20in%20part%20because%20she%20has%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgen-z-career-squeeze-slow-hiring-no-time-for-training-2026-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EGen%20Z%3C%2Fa%3E%20kids%2C%20but%20also%20because%20she's%20worried%20for%20the%20world.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20thing%20that%20scares%20me%20the%20most%20is%20we%20will%20never%20replace%20some%20of%20the%20best%20things%20about%20us%20that%20make%20us%20human%2C%20but%20we%20are%20very%20D-minus%20in%20the%20things%20that%20make%20us%20human%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BAn%20overwhelmed%20citizenry%20will%20default%20to%20hypernormalizing%20and%20choosing%20certainty.%20And%20that%20scares%20me.%20That%20scares%20me%20for%20companies%2C%20but%20it%20really%20scares%20me%20for%20democracy.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fauthor%2Faki-ito%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_self%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cu%3EAki%20Ito%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%20is%20a%20chief%20correspondent%20at%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbrene-brown-interview-silicon-valley-bad-bosses-2026-4%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1777191421000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69ed62a93fecbb42897a41a2%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbrene-b