ey-pwc-deloitte-2025-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Econsulting%20firms%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20partnering%20with%20AI%20startups%20has%20become%20a%20key%20survival%20tactic%20as%20the%20technology%20upends%20everything%20about%20their%20industry.%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EAnd%20for%20AI%20startups%2C%20consulting%20firms%20have%20become%20an%20important%20channel%20for%20distributing%20their%20products%20to%20companies.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20love%20affair%20between%20the%20two%20was%20apparent%20in%20a%20flurry%20of%20recent%20dalliances.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGoogle%20announced%20Wednesday%20it%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Ewas%20launching%20a%20%24750%20million%20fund%20to%20help%20consulting%20firms%20like%20McKinsey%2C%20Accenture%2C%20and%20Deloitte%20roll%20out%20agentic%20AI%20to%20their%20clients.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMcKinsey%20and%20Google%20have%20also%20created%20a%20new%20working%20group%20to%20help%20companies%20go%20from%20identifying%20AI%20opportunities%20to%20building%20and%20scaling%20them%20across%20the%20business.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAlso%20on%20Wednesday%2C%20The%20Wall%20Street%20Journal%20reported%20that%20OpenAI%20was%20working%20with%20consulting%20firms%20like%20Accenture%2C%20Capgemini%2C%20and%20PwC%20to%20sell%20its%20AI%20coding%20assistant%2C%20Codex%2C%20to%20companies.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20rationale%20is%20simple%3A%20AI%20technology%20is%20moving%20so%20fast%20that%20Silicon%20Valley%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fai-mckinsey-consultant-2026-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ethe%20consulting%20industry%3C%2Fa%3E%20need%20each%20other.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBen%20Ellencweig%2C%20a%20senior%20partner%20at%20McKinsey%20who%20leads%20alliances%2C%20acquisitions%2C%20and%20partnerships%20for%20its%20AI%20arm%2C%20Quantum%20Black%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider%20in%20an%20interview%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Ethat%20the%20firm%20has%20quadrupled%20its%20ecosystem%20of%20tech%20partners%20since%20the%20launch%20of%20ChatGPT.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20added%20that%20the%20depth%20of%20the%20firm's%20relationships%20and%20the%20level%20of%20collaboration%20have%20%26quot%3Bgrown%20dramatically%26quot%3B%20in%20the%20past%20few%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20said%20McKinsey%20operates%20an%20%26quot%3Becosystem%20of%20alliances%20and%20acquisitions%26quot%3B%20with%20hundreds%20of%20contributors%2C%20including%20key%20players%20such%20as%20AWS%2C%20Amazon%2C%20Nvidia%2C%20and%20OpenAI%2C%20that%20it%20leverages%20to%20tailor%20solutions%20for%20clients.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAmid%20the%20deluge%20of%20new%20products%20and%20AI%20startups%2C%20Ellencweig%20said%20the%20firm%20still%20adheres%20to%20a%20rigorous%20vetting%20process.%20%26quot%3BThere's%20a%20bit%20of%20a%20dating%20period%20that%20we%20get%20to%20know%20each%20other%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BPartnering%20means%20a%20two-way%20street.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGiven%20the%20pace%20of%20the%20AI%20boom%2C%20however%2C%20he%20said%20the%20firm%20is%20more%20willing%20these%20days%20to%20team%20up%20with%20smaller%20companies.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFormer%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmckinsey-ai-agents-mangement-leadership-great-flattening-2026-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EMcKinsey%20consultants%3C%2Fa%3E%20told%20Business%20Insider%20that%20these%20alliances%20also%20fill%20the%20talent%20gap%20needed%20to%20marry%20the%20raw%20models%20coming%20out%20of%20AI%20labs%20with%20the%20needs%20of%20corporate%20clients.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThese%20consultants%20said%20their%20role%20is%20to%20bring%20these%20models%20to%20the%20enterprise%20level%20%E2%80%94%20customizing%20them%20with%20data%2C%20adding%20appropriate%20guardrails%2C%20and%20helping%20clients%20implement%20them%20in%20specific%20contexts.%20Many%20of%20the%20models%20fresh%20out%20of%20Silicon%20Valley%20simply%20aren't%20enterprise-ready%2C%20consultants%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMcKinsey%20says%20about%2040%25%20of%20its%20work%20now%20comes%20from%20generative%20AI-related%20projects.%20BCG%20said%2020%25%20of%20its%20work%20was%20AI-related%20in%202024.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAndy%20Triedman%2C%20a%20partner%20at%20Theory%20Ventures%2C%20an%20early-stage%20venture%20capital%20firm%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Efocused%20on%20data%20and%20AI%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider%20that%20tech%20startups%20have%20long%20relied%20on%20consulting%20firms%20to%20help%20sell%20their%20products%20to%20enterprise%20clients%2C%20but%20are%20now%20partnering%20much%20earlier%20as%20pressure%20builds%20to%20adapt%20to%20AI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBefore%20ChatGPT%2C%20he%20said%2C%20partnerships%20typically%20happened%20once%20startups%20reached%20%2410%20million%20or%20more%20in%20revenue%20%E2%80%94%20about%20two%20to%20four%20years%20in.%20Now%2C%20they're%20forming%20at%20the%20%242%20million%20to%20%245%20million%20mark%2C%20when%20companies%20are%20only%2012%20to%2018%20months%20old.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETriedman%2C%20a%20former%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsunny-stroeer-bain-consultant-quit-burnout-outdoor-adventure-business-athlete-2026-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EBain%20consultant%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20said%20the%20AI%20ecosystem%20around%20consulting%20firms%20falls%20into%20three%20main%20buckets%3A%20enterprise%20software%20startups%20that%20partner%20with%20consultants%20to%20distribute%20and%20implement%20their%20products%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2F5-ai-powered-consulting-startups-aily-promptql-profound-dialogue-2025-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EAI-native%20consulting%20firms%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20compete%20with%20traditional%20players%2C%20and%20smaller%20AI%20tools%20that%20automate%20core%20consulting%20work%2C%20which%20could%20become%20acquisition%20targets%20for%20bigger%20consulting%20firms.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20a%20mutually%20beneficial%20relationship%20between%20the%20two%2C%26quot%3B%20Triedman%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%